reviewText: I just finished watching The Man Who Couldn't, and wanted to say I loved it. I laughed out loud at the one-liners, and was drawn into the interpersonal relationships. Keep an eye on Brandon Wilson - he's going places.

The Man Who Couldn't is a welcome change from your run of the mill "urban" independent films. The characters are intellectual, bohemian, and diverse. If you are a true lover of cinema, a pessimistic romantic, or just looking for a truly alternative voice in the increasingly homogeneous indy scene, then this is the movie for you.
